node.text:
We celebrate individuality and self expression, and are committed to continue to speak out for equal rights for all individuals to live freely as their most authentic selves. 

We invited artist, educator and gender scholar @matisse.dupont to speak with us about pronoun journeys, exploring your identity, and how to have fun on your path to self-discovery. 

“Don’t worry about finding a label that you’re going to have to be forever that will rewrite your entire past and predict your entire future… You can change and grow as time goes, as you get older, as society changes and new words and terminology become available.” 

There is no wrong way to become the best version of yourself. Enjoy your journey, honor your growth, and don’t forget to always be proud of who you are! #StepIntoLove

node.text: We invited our friends @thetravellinggays to share their inspiring surrogacy journey and remind us that families come in all shapes and sizes. Sending love to fathers of all kinds this upcoming Fathers Day! Whether you’re a dad, a soon-to-be parent or celebrating the father figure in your life, you are appreciated! #AldoCrew #StepintoLove

Today we’re celebrating with @laith_ashley, honoring the history of Pride and also reflecting on the work that still needs to be done to advance equality in our communities and around the world. 

“Whatever color of the rainbow you represent, let’s remember to come together this #Pride to use our strength in numbers, our voice, and our collective, undeniable joy to speak out, loud and proud, for those in our community who need us the most.” 

To learn more about how to take action in support of the LGBTQ+ movement, Laith recommends the @humanrightscampaign and checking in with local organizations in your city or town where your voice can make a big difference. 

Chime in with your favorite organizations and resources below!

node.text:
Let’s talk about Juneteenth, an important holiday taking place in two weeks.
Entrepreneur and Activist @thechelseamiller speaks with us about the importance of recognizing this date as a federal US holiday. 

“Juneteenth is a celebration of what we understand as freedom and the recognition of a delayed promise in this country that for so long has issued this idea of what equity and justice looks like for everyone, but yet it is so delayed for so many.” 

“Juneteenth is an understanding of how we can stand up and show up for a correct storytelling for our history, it is about making sure that we pull up even today for a lot of the issues that are going on in the racial justice space.” 

Visit Chelsea’s IG to learn more about the Juneteenth movement and how we can continue working toward dismantling systems of oppression. And share your favorite local organizers who are mobilizing for Juneteenth recognition below!

node.title: Let’s talk about Juneteenth with Chelsea Miller

We invited @actually_ashly to chat about Mother’s Day and how it’s important to be mindful that Mother’s Day may look different to everyone! 

“Today I celebrate being a fur mom to my girls Ruby and Pepper... but I also celebrate all the amazing people in my life like my own mother, my sisters, friends, and my mentors... who are so special and inspire me everyday!”

We want to send love to mothers of all kinds today and want you to know you are appreciated! 
#AldoCrew #StepintoLove
